Fire: the restless tongue of living red,
It coils and leaps, a wild, mythic beast;
It feeds on air and ancient, splintered wood,
A banquet where all boundaries have ceased.
It calls the distant stars into the room,
Transforms the night with flickers, fierce and bright;
It is both muse and menace, friend and doom—
A fever-dream that dances out of sight.
Let it consume the darkness, let it sing;
In fire’s crackling hymn, all endings ring.
